<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="36.[128,654,1116,1759]" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">
DISTRIBUTION (map 3): Recorded from one locality on the eastern border of southern 
<collectingRegion box="[128,320,1353,1375]" country="Australia" name="South Australia" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">South Australia</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh &amp; C. Weirauch" authorityYear="2010" box="[334,625,1353,1375]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Melaleucoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifoliae">
<emphasis box="[334,625,1353,1375]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">Melaleucoides brevifoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of only two species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh &amp; C. Weirauch" authorityYear="2010" box="[492,654,1382,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Melaleucoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[492,654,1382,1404]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">Melaleucoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group that is known to occur outside 
<collectingRegion box="[128,345,1442,1464]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[128,654,1116,1759]" pageId="36" pageNumber="39">DISCUSSION: All available male specimens for this species were apparently partially teneral, because after several dissections we were unable to find a specimen in which the endosoma was suitably sclerotized for observation and illustration.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
